Problem:
public class WeatherSystem {
    private boolean cloudCover;
    private boolean rain;
    public void setCloudCover(boolean cloud) {
        this.cloudCover = cloud;
        if (cloud) {
            System.out.println('Clouds have formed.');
            this.rain = true;
        }
    }
    public boolean isRaining() {
        return rain;
    }
    public void clearSkies() {
        cloudCover = false;
        rain = false;
        System.out.println('Skies are clear now.');
    }
}",

If a method intervenes to forcefully set cloudCover to false, will it stop raining?
